text.tspan: Death rate in armed conflicts based on where they occurred
Deaths of combatants and civilians due to fighting, per 100,000 people. Included are interstate, intrastate,
extrasystemic, non-state conflicts, and one-sided violence.
Data source: Uppsala Conflict Data Program (2024); Natural Earth (2022); Population based on various sources (2024)
